{{unreferenced|date=June 2018}}
{{orphan|date=March 2017}}
'''John Alexander''' was a well-known [[Medical Officer for Health|medical health officer]] for the county of [[Caithness]], [[North Scotland]] until his death on December 5, 1901.

Alexander married Georgina Duguid, of [[Aberdeenshire]]. His brother, Alexander Alexander, was also in the [[medical industry]].

A few years after John Alexander's death, a monument in [[Wick (Caithness)|Wick]] was erected in his memory. It still stands today on a small hill beside the local railway station. Alexander's [[grave]] is located in Watten Cemetery, where he is buried alongside his wife, two nephews, his great nephew, and his second great niece.

