{{infobox company | name = Open Bionics | logo = Ob logo (1).jpg | type = [[Private company]] | traded_as = | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = | founder = | defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | location_city = Bristol | location_country = United Kingdom | location = | locations = | area_served = | key_people = {{plainlist| * Joel Gibbard <small>[[Chief executive officer|CEO]]</small> * Samantha Payne <small>[[Chief operating officer|COO]]</small> }} | industry = [[Medical devices]], [[healthcare]] | products = 3D printed bionic prosthetics | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{url|https://www.openbionics.com|www.openbionics.com}} | footnotes = | intl = }}
'''Open Bionics''', founded in 2014, is a UK based company developing low-cost [[bionic]] hands. It is based inside Future Space, co-located with [[Bristol Robotics Laboratory]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.futurespacebristol.co.uk/2016/09/14/open-bionics/|title=Future Space Case Studies - Open Bionics|last=|first=|date=|website=www.brl.ac.uk|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2016-02-03}}</ref> [[File:Star_Wars_Bionic_hand.jpg|thumbnail|A 3D printed Star Wars bionic hand by Open Bionics in collaboration with ILM XLab.]]
In 2015 [[Disney]] and the company announced a partnership to create superhero-themed prosthetics for young amputees.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Open Bionics and Disney release Star Wars, Iron Man and Frozen themed prosthetics|url = https://www.wired.co.uk/news/archive/2015-10/13/disney-open-bionics-prosthetics|website = Wired UK|access-date = 2016-02-03}}</ref>
In 2015 the company won a [[James Dyson Award]] for innovative engineering 2015<ref>{{Cite web|title = Open Bionics 3D-printed robotic hand wins Dyson Award|url = https://www.wired.co.uk/news/archive/2015-08/25/open-bionics-james-dyson-award|website = Wired UK|access-date = 2016-02-03}}</ref> and a [[Tech4Good awards|Tech4Good]] award.<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|title = Winners 2015 - Tech4Good Awards|url = http://www.tech4goodawards.com/winners-2015/|website = Tech4Good Awards|access-date = 2016-02-03|language = en-US}}</ref> In 2016 it won a [[Bloomberg Business News|Bloomberg Business]] Innovators award.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Open Bionics - Bloomberg Business Innovators|url = https://www.bloomberg.com/ukinnovators/innovators/open-bionics/|access-date = 2016-02-03}}</ref>
