{{Infobox medical condition (new) | synonyms = Short stature wormian bones dextrocardia | name = Stratton-Parker Syndrome | image = | image_width = | image_caption = | symptoms = | complications = | onset = | duration = | types = | causes = | risks = | diagnosis = | differential = | prevention = | treatment = | medication = | prognosis = | frequency = | deaths = }}
'''Stratton parker syndrome''' is a rare disorder characterized by short stature, [[wormian bones]] (extra cranial bones), and [[dextrocardia]] (displaced heart).<ref name="orphan">{{cite web| publisher=Check Orphan| title=Short stature wormian bones dextrocardia| accessdate=2011-09-27| url=http://checkorphan.com/disease/short-stature-wormian-bones-dextrocardia}}</ref> Other symptoms include [[dermatoglyphics]], tooth deformities or missing teeth, abnormal kidney development, shortened limbs, mental retardation, undescended testes or [[cryptorchidism]], and [[anal atresia]].<ref name="orphan"/> The condition was first described by Stratton and Parker in 1989,<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Stratton RF, Parker MW |title=Growth hormone deficiency, wormian bones, dextrocardia, brachycamptodactyly, and other midline defects |journal=American Journal of Medical Genetics |volume=32 |issue=2 |pages=169–73 |date=February 1989 |doi=10.1002/ajmg.1320320205 |pmid=2564736 }}</ref> and there have been only four reported cases worldwide.<ref>{{cite web| publisher=Endocrine Abstracts| title=Growth hormone deficiency and complex congenital abnormalities: a further case of Stratton-Parker syndrome?| last1=Simmgen| first1=M.| last2=Bano| first2=G.| last3=Nussey| first3=S.| year=2006| volume=12| id=P86| accessdate=2011-09-27| url=http://www.endocrine-abstracts.org/ea/0012/ea0012p86.htm}}</ref> Two cases of the syndrome were reported by [[Gilles-Eric Seralini]] in 2010 after having been contacted in January 2009.<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Mesnage | first1 = R. | last2 = Clair | first2 = E. | last3 = Spiroux De Vendomois | first3 = J. | last4 = Seralini | first4 = G. E. | title = Two cases of birth defects overlapping Stratton-Parker syndrome after multiple pesticide exposure | doi = 10.1136/oem.2009.052969 | journal = Occupational and Environmental Medicine | volume = 67 | issue = 5 | pages = 359 | year = 2009 | pmid = 19951932| pmc = }}</ref>
Alternative names include "Growth Hormone Deficiency with Wormian Bones, Cardiac Anomaly, and Brachycamptodactyly"<ref>{{cite web| publisher=BioGraph| title=STRATTON-PARKER SYNDROME| accessdate=2011-09-27| url=http://www.biograph.be/concept/show/C1861448}}</ref> and "Short stature wormian bones dextrocardia"<ref name="orphan"/>
